    "In terms of completeness, approximately 62.3% of the generated reports had no missing content.",
    "In 31.0% of the reports, there were minor instances of missing content, such as extremely small lesions.",
    "However, 6.7% of reports had a significant amount of missing content, primarily due to unclear imaging leading to false negatives.",
    "Examples of different grades of generated reports are shown in Supplementary Fig. 2.",
    "After the first stage evaluation of report generation, we identified 20 out of 31 conditions (approximately 64.5%) that received positive feedback in the professional assessment."
